cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it deals with analyzing the influence of a Twitter account, which is a social network. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) as it deals with social media behavior. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves analyzing and evaluating data from Twitter accounts. It could also be classified under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) as it involves analyzing online behavior and visibility. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it involves analyzing and evaluating multimedia content on Twitter.
